    {
        "chapter": 14,
        "act": 2,
        "name": "A Fractured Legion",
        "startVideo": "tfh_ch14",
        "endVideo": "tfh_ch14post",
        "startDialogue": "<dl><dd><b>Laaneth:</b> <i>\"If the locals weren't lying, the Legion should be nearby.\"</i></dd>\n<dd><b>Swims-at-Night:</b> <i>\"There they are!\"</i></dd>\n<dd><b>Tyr:</b> <i>\"Hail! I am Tyr, knight brother of the Blades.\"</i></dd>\n<dd><b>Swims-at-Night:</b> <i>\"They don't look pleased to see us.\"</i></dd></dl>",
        "endDialogue": "<dl><dd><b>Legate Cassia:</b> <i>\"Well, look who it is. Thanks for taking out those deserters for me, Tyr. Have you come to serve the Emperor once more?\"</i></dd>\n<dd><b>Tyr:</b> <i>\"Cassia. We need to speak with him immediately.\"</i></dd>\n<dd><b>Kellen:</b> <i>\"The emperor was horrified to hear of Lord Naarifin's plan. But he knew an attack on the Imperial City was doomed to fail.\"</i></dd>\n<dd><b>Kellen:</b> <i>\"Somehow the Dominion could predict his forces' every move. The hero volunteered to infiltrate the city, and discover the source of this ability.\"</i></dd>\n<dd><b>Nagh:</b> <i>\"Was the city not guarded?\"</i></dd>\n<dd><b>Kellen:</b> <i>\"Ah! Well, you see, Naarifin had recently reopened the Arena. The hero resolved to pose as a gladiator to gain entry. Once inside, Swims-at-Night would lead them to a secret passageway into the White-Gold Tower.\"</i></dd></dl>",
